702788f-b.title: Brooklyn: 58th Street (East) - Kings Highway
702788f-b.text:
5769 East 58th Street, at the south east intersection of King's Highway and Church Ave. A view of the modernized farm-house, known as the John Remsen Farwwhouse, also known as the Peter Remsen Farm-hoise. It was built in 1797- by Johannus Remsen (1793-1868) who marriod Catherine Schenck daughter of Tunis Schenck, one of the original settlers of gew Utrecht. The rear extension to the house was erected in 1865.
March 1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
